WEBVTT

00:02:29.715 --> 00:02:31.212
And more to the point:

00:02:31.236 --> 00:02:34.691
With all of this creative talent,
what more could we do?

00:02:36.556 --> 00:02:38.865
Just as I was about to start
my final exams,

00:02:38.889 --> 00:02:41.589
I decided to take a break
from an all-nighter

00:02:42.018 --> 00:02:44.930
and go to a lecture by Dr. Paul Farmer,

00:02:45.514 --> 00:02:48.510
a leading health activist
for the global poor.

00:02:48.534 --> 00:02:52.316
I was surprised to hear a doctor
talking about architecture.

00:02:52.340 --> 00:02:54.822
Buildings are making
people sicker, he said,

00:02:54.846 --> 00:02:56.639
and for the poorest in the world,

00:02:56.663 --> 00:02:59.559
this is causing epidemic-level problems.

